doc.title: August speeds to decrease 7% to 7.0CPR (VPR down 7%)

passages.text: As per the latest GSE daily reporting data, August speeds thus far have tracked mostly in line with July for the most recent reporting days. Based on 16 days of data (through 8/22), the overall aggregated 30- year CPR is projected to decrease by 7% to 7.0CPR in August, assuming day count adjusted curtailment and unchanged buyout rate from July. The overall 30yr VPR is projected to decrease by 7% MoM.

The current projected change of - 7% roughly in line with the BofA prepayment model projection, which forecasts a 7% speed decrease MoM. The model forecast is mainly driven by the 7% seasonal slowdown, a 1- day decline in day count, slightly offset by 6bps decline in driving mortgage rate. (Agency MBS Prepayment Outlook: August speeds to decrease 7% to 6.8CPR 14 August 2025)
For 30yr TBA eligible pools, speeds are expected to decline MoM across the stack by 4- 11%. Coupon 2.5s see largest decline by 11% while 6s and 6.5s see slightly smaller decline by 4%.
Black Knight projections indicate 10% MoM CPR decrease based on 15 collection days, suggesting slower speeds than BofA's estimate of - 7% and also slightly slower than GSE estimate of - 7%.
